1.7.2 Is Java case sensitive?
      What is the case for Java keywords?
=== ANS ===
Java is case sensitive language i.e. class Complex and class complex are two different
treated as two different classes by Java compiler.

Java keywords are all written in lowercase.


1.7.3 What is a comment?
      Is the comment ignored by the compiler?
      How do you denote a comment line and a comment paragraph?
=== ANS ===
Comment is a sequence of characters which are ignored by Java compiler.
Comment main purpose it to comment hard to understand or logic thought of piece of code.
In Java there are 3 flavors of comments:
Single line comment: starts with // all characters after it till the end of the line is comment.
Multiple line comment: starts with /* and will be a comment until */ is encountered.


